:INFO
The Novel That Is Not About What You Think It Is About
I came to It expecting a horror novel about a supernatural clown. What I found \
was a novel about seven children in a small Maine town who face something they \
cannot name or explain, and who grow up and have to go back. The horror is real \
and often genuinely frightening. But the central subject of the book is memory: \
how what happened to you in childhood shapes everything that comes after, and \
what it costs to return to the place where it happened.

